"summary": "According to Hans Bunting, COO of renewables at Innogy SE, new nuclear power stations in the UK can no longer compete with wind farms on price due to advances in wind turbine technology. Despite criticism over the £30bn cost to consumers for EDF Energy’s Hinkley Point C nuclear power station, EDF argues that nuclear power is also on a path to lower costs. The price of wind power is set to decrease further with the development of bigger turbines, which can reduce costs by requiring fewer turbines for the same capacity and using less steel and cables."
}

